.TH CATOPY 1 "May 2026" "catopy 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
catopy \- copy file contents to the system clipboard safely
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B catopy
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " FILE"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B catopy
reads text from a file and places it in the system clipboard.
It includes size guards to avoid accidentally copying very large files.
On Linux, clipboard handoff uses a short wait to improve reliability for short-lived processes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --head " " N
Copy only the first N lines.
.TP
.BR --tail " " N
Copy only the last N lines.
.TP
.B --force
Bypass the file size guard.
.TP
.BR --max-bytes " " SIZE
Maximum file size before refusing copy. Supports suffixes K, M, G.
.TP
.B --no-color
Disable ANSI color output.
.TP
.BR -h , " " --help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR -V , " " --version
Print version information.
.SH CONFIG FILE
Optional configuration file:
.I ~/.catopy.rc
.PP
Supported keys:
.TP
.B behave_as_cat
If true, prints copied content to stdout.
.TP
.B warning_size_limit
Default maximum file size guard.
.TP
.B default_head
Default value for --head.
.TP
.B default_tail
Default value for --tail.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Copy full file:
.B catopy notes.txt
.TP
Copy first 20 lines:
.B catopy --head 20 /var/log/messages
.TP
Copy last 100 lines:
.B catopy --tail 100 app.log
.TP
Override limit:
.B catopy --max-bytes 5M dump.txt
.SH AUTHOR
catopy maintainers.
